        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T15:57:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027ve ignored the variable \"count\".\n\nThe idea behind this variable is that readRows is currently called in two places: onGetPixels, when we\u0027re decoding the entire image, and onGetScanlines, when we\u0027re decoding some subset of the image.\n\nMy intent is for incremental decoding to replace scanline decoding (i.e. onStartScanlineDecode, onGetScanlines, onSkipScanlines). If we remove those, readRows no longer needs the parameter.\n\nThat also means this method needs to take into account sampling and skip lines if we\u0027re sampling. (See SkPngCodec.cpp and SkGifCodec.cpp, which both do this. Look for calls to sampleY().)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 482,
        "startChar": 82,
        "endLine": 482,
        "endChar": 91
      },
      "revId": "28ed1d604ca0b861631ecf1da6192ea3e3619fcf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4d04d608_9a354d0b",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkJpegCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 490,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T15:57:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The comment says rowbytes, but you\u0027re using dstInfo.width(). You should use rowBytes here, in case the memory has padding.\n\nWe can also use a template method (used down below) that makes this a little cleaner:\n\n  dst \u003d SkTAddOffset\u003cvoid\u003e(dst, output_scanline * rowBytes);",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 490,
        "startChar": 67,
        "endLine": 490,
