    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1d5749b5_9e80c8a8",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkJpegCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 525,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T15:57:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The original intent of this return value is to tell how many lines were decoded. This way, if less than count lines were decoded, the caller knows to fill in the rest with something. But since we\u0027re drawing progressively, I\u0027m not sure this is necessarily the right value. For a sequential JPEG, this is correct, but for a progressive JPEG, I\u0027m guessing that on the second pass we want to set this to height, since the whole thing has been initialized.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 525,
        "startChar": 41,
        "endLine": 525,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "28ed1d604ca0b861631ecf1da6192ea3e3619fcf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "514fb4e4_bc6e1273",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkJpegCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 807,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-07T15:57:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This should be kErrorInInput, since we have (potentially) decoded part of the image. (We\u0027ve been somewhat inconsistent about this, and kErrorInInput is a new value. See skbug.com/6825.)\n\nWe also need to set rowsDecoded to how many lines have been initialized. See code in SkPngCodec.cpp and SkGifCodec.cpp.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 807,
        "startChar": 52,
        "endLine": 807,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "28ed1d604ca0b861631ecf1da6192ea3e3619fcf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
